Reasoning: The paper deals with graph classes modeled by families of non-crossing connected sets, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The focus on forbidden induced subgraph characterizations and linear time certifying recognition algorithms suggests computational geometry (cs.CG) as another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the dominating set problem and Hamiltonian cycles and paths, which are topics in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The study of graph classes and their properties also falls under graph theory (cs.GT) and combinatorics (cs.CC).
